「建築」を「生産」産業の視点から考える授業です。建築を豪華な一品モノの作品として捉えるのではなく、モジュール・システムや生産工程など、「インダストリアル」や「量産」という観点から捉えた切り口で、みんなと一緒に考えて行く授業です。 プレハブ建築、移動建築、軽量建築、極限建築、宇宙建築、コンポーネント設計、インフレータブル建築、被膜建築、3Dプリント建築、などのケース・スタディーを通して、自分たちでも何か新しい発想のプロダクト・建築を考えます。

The moment of Architectural Awakening is when Buckminster Fuller questioned “How much do your building weigh?”

In B.B. (Before Bucky era:), construction was hopelessly heavy and builders were the prisoner of the gravity. The Prisoner was simply pilling heavy stones or bricks or pouring concrete in a mold for making heavier base. Making dome and vault was the great escape from the gravity, but still material, in B.B. era, pulled human’s creativity down to the gravity field.

In present, we are about gaining new material with new way of construction. Pre- fab house, air structure, tensile structure, honey comb panel, carbon fiber, space frame, ETFE membrane etc. The material triggered the architectural revolution that widen the production process of the building today.

We are going to focus on “production process” of architecture. In my architectural point of view, sculpt the shape of the building is the last thing that makes me excited. Beyond the styling, there are many elements that forms architectural design. Therefore we are not going to investigate the architecture as one article of gorgeousness matter. Our study will be engaged with its “Production”, “Transportation”, “Installation”, “Material” and “Function”.

Our scope of the building type is Industrialized Architecture. Understanding how our industry developed the effective deployment of architecture through the case study. E.g. Pre-Fabricated / Mass-Produced architecture, portable, light-weight, component, container, inflatable, membrane, tensegrity, 3Dprint architecture.

Assignment of this class is to design/experience the new way of building construction process.

The Course is only open for Believer who thinks the functional design is the colorful spice for a design industry, and Creative thinker who can enjoy Sketching, Modeling, Discussing and making Failure with Positive mind.

